<category term="NES Graphics" scheme="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewforum.php?f=21" label="NES Graphics"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=18293&amp;p=231874#p231874"><![CDATA[
Black outlines are useful for the restrictions of blurry NTSC color artifacting.  By using a monochrome outline, you avoid color collisions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Jan 10, 2019 10:04 am</p><hr />
